    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix blocking issue in rrc_enb_process_itti_msg when called from rrc_rx_tx\n\n### Summary\nThe `rrc_enb_process_itti_msg()` function was designed as an infinite message processing loop for the RRC eNB task. However, it was also being called directly from `rrc_rx_tx()`, which caused the calling function to block indefinitely waiting for more messages that may never arrive.\n\nThis fix separates the message processing logic into a reusable helper function and creates a new non-blocking variant for use in contexts like `rrc_rx_tx()`.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_eNB.c`: \n  - Created `rrc_enb_process_one_itti_msg()` helper function containing the message processing logic\n  - Modified `rrc_enb_process_itti_msg()` to use the helper in its loop\n  - Added `rrc_enb_process_itti_msg_one_shot()` function that processes available messages without blocking\n  - Updated `rrc_rx_tx()` to call the new one-shot function instead of the blocking version\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_proto.h`: Added function prototype for `rrc_enb_process_itti_msg_one_shot()`\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running the OAI eNB with active UEs, calling procedures that trigger `rrc_rx_tx()` (such as periodic subframe processing) would cause the function to hang indefinitely. This manifested as:\n- No response to subsequent RRC messages from UEs\n- MAC layer becoming unresponsive\n- Eventually leading to timeout errors in the S1AP connection\n\nThe issue was particularly noticeable during handover procedures or when processing RRC reconfigurations, where the system would appear to freeze after sending a `RRC_SUBFRAME_PROCESS` message.\n"
}